GSEAPlots

Source: R/GSEAPlots.R
GSEAPlots.Rd

Visualization of GSEA or ORA

Usage

GSEAPlots(
  gseData,
  Fraction,
  enrich = c("gsea", "ora"),
  plotType = c("dotPlot", "cNetPlot", "heatPlot", "treePlot", "gseaPlot", "ridgePlot"),
  circular = FALSE,
  colorEdge = FALSE,
  nodeLabel = c("gene", "category", "all", "none"),
  cexLabelCategory = 1.2,
  cexLabelGene = 0.8,
  colorCcategory = "black",
  colorGene = "black",
  showCategory = 10,
  org = "dme",
  pvalCutOff = 0.05
)

Arguments

gseData

Output from clusterProfiler (as list)

Fraction

Can be either "Proteome" or "Enriched". Indicates the type of input data used

plotType

Can be one of "dotPlot", "cNetPlot", "heatPlot", "treePlot", "gseaPlot", "ridgePlot"

circular

Logical, default is FALSE. If TRUE, circular visualization will be used for cNetPlot

colorEdge

Logical, default is FALSE. Parameter to be used if circular = "TRUE" and plotType ' "cNetPlot

nodeLabel

Can be one of "gene", "category", "all", "none". Parameter to be used if circular = "TRUE" and plotType ' "cNetPlot

cexLabelCategory

Parameter to be used if circular = "TRUE" and plotType ' "cNetPlot (Check enrichplot package for further info). Defaults i 1.2

cexLabelGene

Parameter to be used if circular = "TRUE" and plotType ' "cNetPlot (Check enrichplot package for further info). Default is 0.8

colorCcategory

Parameter to be used if circular = "TRUE" and plotType ' "cNetPlot (Check enrichplot package for further info). Default is "black"

colorGene

Parameter to be used if circular = "TRUE" and plotType ' "cNetPlot (Check enrichplot package for further info). Default is "black"

showCategory

Number of GO terms to be displayed in the plot. Default is 10

org

Database of the organism. Drosophila melanogaster = "dme", Mus muscuslus ' "mmu", Homo sapiens = "hsa", Saccharomyces cerevisae = "sce". Default is "dme"

pvalCutOff

P-value cut off for significant protein(s), site(s) and GO terms. Default is 0.05

Value

Generates plots from GO term analysis
